LGTM. Regarding tests;

RayInstaller seems like it doesn't really need testing assuming there are already tests for NodeUpdater. If we have any error handling in that layer, we may want 

For NodeProvierAdapter, I guess we can write some unit tests with mocks, but it doesn't seem that valuable rn (since the logic is straightforward. Maybe when we have error handling code, we can write some tests with mock)? The actual test probably needs to be done in underlying provider (which I believe it is already done).

def __cmp__(self, other):
        if isinstance(other, GUID):
            return cmp()(binary(self), binary(other))
        return -1

